  "prompt": "Can dogs digest bones?",
  "response": "Dogs can partially digest bones, but it's not without risks:\n\n1. Raw bones are generally safer than cooked bones\n- Cooked bones can splinter and cause internal injuries\n- Raw bones are softer and more digestible\n\n2. Potential risks include:\n- Choking\n- Intestinal blockage\n- Broken teeth\n- Punctured digestive tract\n\n3. Some bones are safer than others:\n- Large raw beef or bison bones are typically safer\n- Small bones or cooked bones are more dangerous\n\n4. Veterinarian recommendations:\n- Supervise dogs when giving bones\n- Choose appropriately sized bones\n- Consider bone alternatives like dental chews\n- Consult your vet about safe bone options\n\n5. Digestibility depends on:\n- Dog's size\n- Bone type\n- Bone preparation\n- Individual dog's digestive system\n\nWhile dogs can digest some bones, it's important to be cautious and informed about potential risks.",
